# .scannerignore - Paths to exclude from Intellicrack production scanner
# Lines starting with # are comments, one path per line
#
# =============================================================================
# PATTERN RECOGNITION - What's Now Auto-Detected
# =============================================================================
#
# The scanner automatically recognizes these patterns (NO MANUAL IGNORES NEEDED):
#
# 1. Abstract Methods (completely excluded):
#    - Functions with @abstractmethod or @abc.abstractmethod decorators
#    - Methods in ABC subclasses that raise NotImplementedError
#    - Pass-only methods in abstract base classes
#
# 2. CLI Framework Commands (completely excluded):
#    - Click: @click.group(), @click.command(), @cli.command()
#    - Typer: @app.command()
#    - Argparse: Command group patterns
#
# 3. Orchestration Patterns (50% confidence reduction):
#    - Functions with ≥3 function calls coordinating workflow
#    - Functions with progress reporting and result aggregation
#    - High-level controllers that delegate to other functions
#
# 4. Delegation Patterns (50% confidence reduction):
#    - Wrapper functions (≤3 lines) that add error handling, logging, or validation
#    - Functions that delegate to others with added value
#
# 5. Validation Functions (deduction points applied):
#    - Functions using isinstance(), hasattr(), type() checks
#    - Functions checking Path.exists(), is_file(), os.access()
#
# =============================================================================
# When Manual Ignores Are Still Needed
# =============================================================================
#
# Use .scannerignore for entire directories/files, or scanner-ignore comments
# for individual functions when:
#
# 1. LLM Delegation Patterns (not yet auto-detected):
#    - Functions that call llm.chat(), llm.generate(), etc.
#    - Use: # scanner-ignore: LLM delegation
#
# 2. External Tool Integration:
#    - Functions that delegate to subprocess/external tools
#    - Use: # scanner-ignore: Delegates to radare2
#
# 3. Test Files/Helpers:
#    - Test fixtures, mock data generators
#    - Add test directories below or use scanner-ignore comments
#
# 4. Generated Code:
#    - Auto-generated bindings, protobuf files, etc.
#    - Add directories below
#
# 5. Third-Party Code:
#    - Vendored dependencies, external libraries
#    - Add directories below
#
# =============================================================================
# Scanner-Ignore Comment Syntax
# =============================================================================
#
# For individual functions, use this syntax on the line BEFORE the function:
#
#     # scanner-ignore: Reason for ignoring
#     def my_function():
#         return llm.chat("prompt")
#
# NOTE: Only use scanner-ignore for legitimate patterns, NOT to hide real stubs!
#
# =============================================================================
# Path Exclusions Below
# =============================================================================

